NAME
mdb â€” Sample SQL database for nonprofit inventory tracking, kit assembly, and outreach logistics
SYNOPSIS
USE mdb;


DESCRIPTION
The mdb database is designed for ACCW Mauiâ€™s nonprofit operations. It tracks donations, inventory, purchases, kit composition, and distribution events. All data is mock and intended for instructional use in IT125 SQL Project.

TABLES
Donor
Stores donor contact info and donation details.
Primary Key: donor_id
Fields:
- donoation_type: ENUM('Food', 'Clothing', 'Money')
- donation_date: DATETIME
- Linked to Item via donor_id

Item
Tracks inventory items, source, condition, and donor linkage.
Primary Key: item_id
Fields:
- item_category: ENUM('Food', 'Hygiene', 'Clothing')
- source_type: ENUM('Donated', 'Purchased', 'Assembled')
- item_condition: ENUM('Poor', 'Fair', 'Good', 'Null')
- is_kit: BOOLEAN
- FK: donor_id â†’ Donor(donor_id)

Location
Defines physical locations for storage or outreach.
Primary Key: location_id
Fields:
- location_city: ENUM of Maui towns

User
Stores staff/volunteer info for accountability.
Primary Key: user_id
Fields:
- user_role: VARCHAR(45)

Purchase
Logs purchases from vendors.
Primary Key: purchase_id
Fields:
- invoice_number, purchase_total, vendor_name
- Linked to Item via Item_Purchase

Reorder_Threshold
Defines minimum stock levels for items.
Primary Key: item_id
FK: item_id â†’ Item(item_id)

Order_List
Tracks restocking orders and status.
Primary Key: order_id
Fields:
- status: ENUM('Pending', 'Ordered', 'Received')
- FK: item_id â†’ Item(item_id)

Kit / Kit_Item
Defines kits and their item composition.
Primary Key: kit_id
Kit_Item: Composite PK (kit_id, item_id)
- FK: kit_id â†’ Kit(kit_id)
- FK: item_id â†’ Item(item_id)

Distribution_Method
Lists outreach channels.
Primary Key: method_id
Fields:
- method_name: ENUM('Mobile Van', 'Food Bank', 'Church', 'Event')

Distribution_Event
Logs outreach events.
Primary Key: event_id
FKs:
- method_id â†’ Distribution_Method(method_id)
- location_id â†’ Location(location_id)
- user_id â†’ User(user_id)

Distribution_Log
Records items distributed at events.
Primary Key: log_id (AUTO_INCREMENT)
FKs:
- item_id â†’ Item(item_id)
- event_id â†’ Distribution_Event(event_id)

Item_Purchase
Junction table linking items to purchases.
Composite PK: (item_id, purchase_id)
FKs:
- item_id â†’ Item(item_id)
- purchase_id â†’ Purchase(purchase_id)

USAGE EXAMPLES
- Add a donor: INSERT INTO Donor (...) VALUES (...);
- Add inventory: INSERT INTO Item (...) VALUES (...);
- Log a distribution: INSERT INTO Distribution_Log (...) VALUES (...);
- Trigger reorder alert: SELECT ... FROM Item JOIN Reorder_Threshold WHERE item_qty < min_quantity;

